The paper discusses the design and evaluation of a human computation game, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also explores the social conditions and scoring mechanics that affect players' experiences, which could be categorized under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits and tradeoffs of these mechanics in HCG design, which could be related to cybernetics (cs.CY) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
